    <div class="entry first">
    
      <h3><a href="/thekitchn/sweets/melt-in-your-mouth-8-tempting-recipes-for-fudge-160557">Melt in Your Mouth: <em>8 Tempting Recipes for Fudge</em></a></h3>

        
      <div class="content">

<p><a href="http://www.thekitchn.com/thekitchn/sweets/melt-in-your-mouth-8-tempting-recipes-for-fudge-160557"><img alt="2011-11-11-Fudge.jpg" src="http://i-cdn.apartmenttherapy.com/uimages/kitchen/2011-11-11-Fudge.jpg" width="540" height="423" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0 auto 20px;" /></a>Do any of you make fudge? I always associate this thick, chewy, melt-in-your-mouth candy with the holiday season, but it's actually been years since I've had any. Time to revive the tradition!</p>
          <p class="clearfix">
            <a
              href="http://twitter.com/share"
              class="twitter-share-button tweet-home"
              target="_blank"
              data-url="http://www.thekitchn.com/thekitchn/sweets/melt-in-your-mouth-8-tempting-recipes-for-fudge-160557"
              data-text="Melt in Your Mouth: 8 Tempting Recipes for Fudge"
              data-count="horizontal"
              data-via="thekitchn"> </a>

                              <a
                  href="#fb-like"
                  class="facebook_stub"
                  data-url="http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thekitchn.com%2Fthekitchn%2Fsweets%2Fmelt-in-your-mouth-8-tempting-recipes-for-fudge-160557"> </a>
              
              <g:plusone size="medium" href="http://www.thekitchn.com/thekitchn/sweets/melt-in-your-mouth-8-tempting-recipes-for-fudge-160557" count="true"></g:plusone>

          </p>

      </div>

        <div class="floater">
        	<div id='div-gpt-ad-1320766135777-0'>
		<script type='text/javascript'>
			googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1320766135777-0'); });
		</script>
	</div>      </div>
  
      <div class="content extended">
<p>Fudge can be as finicky or as easy-peasy as you like it. Traditional recipes require candy thermometers and include instructions for cooling the fudge on marble slabs. But the ones that take a few shortcuts are very often just as good. </p>

<p>I also love how endlessly adaptable fudge can be. You can take a basic recipe, like chocolate or vanilla fudge, and mix in whatever extras you have around. Pretzels, candy bits, nuts, dried fruits, and the contents of <a href="http://www.thekitchn.com/thekitchn/quick-reference-a-guide-to-herbs-and-spices-108770">your spice drawer</a> are all fair game here. </p>

<p>Here are some recipes to inspire your holiday fudge-making:</p>

<p>&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.marthastewart.com/333113/simple-chocolate-fudge#">Simple Chocolate Fudge</a> from Martha Stewart</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.saveur.com/article/Recipes/Vanilla-Cream-Fudge">Vanilla Cream Fudge</a> from Saveur</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://leitesculinaria.com/4502/recipes-maple-pecan-fudge.html">Maple Pecan Fudge</a> from Leite's Culinaria</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.bonappetit.com/recipes/2005/03/bittersweet_chocolate_and_walnut_fudge">Bittersweet Chocolate and Walnut Fudge</a> from Bon App&eacute;tit</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/2010/03/coconut-milk-fudge/">Coconut Milk Fudge</a> from Smitten Kitchen</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.myrecipes.com/recipe/mocha-almond-fudge-10000001873414/">Mocha Almond Fudge</a> from Sunset Magazine/MyRecipes</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.finecooking.com/recipes/rocky-road-fudge.aspx">Rocky Road Fudge</a> from Fine Cooking</strong><br />
&bull; <strong><a href="http://www.bakerella.com/peanut-butter-fudge/">Peanut Butter Fudge</a> from Bakerella</strong></p>

<p>What's your favorite kind of fudge?</p>

<p><strong>Related:</strong> <a href="http://www.thekitchn.com/thekitchn/dessert/how-to-make-candied-bacon-fudge-102780">How to Make Candied Bacon Fudge</a></p>

<p><small>(Image: <a href="http://www.marthastewart.com/333113/simple-chocolate-fudge#">Martha Stewart</a>)</small></p>
      </div>


