    <div class="comment">
	    <a name="cid-1399310"></a>
	    <p class="text">My go-to fudge recipe is dead simple to make and to customize, and is delicious.  Mix 2/3 cup evaporated milk and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a big saucepan, add a large pinch of salt, and bring to a boil, stirring.  Turn down heat and simmer another 5 min, then remove from heat.  Immediately stir in a 12-oz bag of chocolate chips until all melted, then any mix-ins you want -- extracts, nuts, marshmallows, dried fruit, peanut butter, whatever.  Spread in a greased 8x8 pan (9x13 for a double batch), let cool, and enjoy!<br><br>I love this made with dark chocolate chips and orange extract, and it's great with mint or with raspberries.  I can't tell you how well it keeps, though, because it has vanished quickly every time I've made it.</p>
      <div class="meta">
        posted by
	      	        <a href="http://community.apartmenttherapy.com/users/122923">
